deck: A young girl that can transform into a wolfman. She insists she isn't a werewolf.
description:
History

Good Silva lived in Detroit, Michigan with her brother, Lucky Silva, and their parents until supervillains attacked their neighborhood destroying their house. Lucky was injured in the blast caused by Firebrand. Seeing their neighbors across the street being harassed by Pitchfork, Good confronted the villain by changing into her wolf form.

After the neighborhood incident, Good went and stayed with Lucky at the hospital. She watched the news and saw Councilman Dick Snerd praising the villains as heroes for the particularly high crime neighborhoods they were attacking. Good then decided to make a visit downtown. Soon afterwards, Good was brought into the jail by two policeman for throwing a glass bottle at Snerd. She tried to get them to let go of her, stating they were hurting her arm, when she changed into her wolf form. Good tried to leave the police station but the exit was quickly blocked by police with guns drawn. Behind her was the Great Lakes Avengers who had earlier been arrested for having gotten into a brawl at the nightclub Baphomet, owned by a supervillain by the name of Nain Rouge. The team had broken out of their cell to protect both Good Boy and the police. Connie Ferrari, the Avengers attorney, had the GLA released from jail and made Good a temporary member of the team until she could figure out what to do with her.

Good's first 'assignment' was to go with Big Bertha to the nightclub Baphomet to see if they can find any leads since the supervillains were seen hanging out there. Inside they find Dick Snerd passed out drunk with Nain Rouge's mask beside him. Good and Bertha take Snerd to GLA HQ and tie him up in the store room. Snerd tells them how he used to be a superhero like them until he was injured and he joined the city council. After Snerd shared his origin, Bertha stepped out to get coffee and left Good to watch over him. Good was still angry over what happened to her brother, however, and allowed Snerd to goad her into attacking him. Connie Ferrari came by to discuss legal maneuvers against an injunction placed on the team by Snerd earlier that day, not knowing the councilman had been abducted. Hearing some commotion in the store room, Connie found Good with a severely injured Dick Snerd. Thinking quickly, the team rolled Snerd in a rug, tied it with rope, and left him outside the hospital.

That same night, Lucky left the hospital on his own and tracked Good to GLA HQ. In an effort to protect Good, Lucky left Detroit with her. However, when Good received word that Bertha needed help with Dr. Nod, Good left Lucky at a gas station, having snuck out a bathroom window and headed back to Detroit.

deck: Owner of a warehouse that the Muse used for one of their pieces in New York.
description:
Frederick Durnin is the owner of a warehouse that was used by the Muse for one of their ghoulish pieces of art. Freddy decided to contact a friend of his by the name of Cassius Grover a former art professor to see if he could sell the piece of art. Councilwoman Andrea Pearson was against this decision and made a call to the District Attorney, Benjamin Hochberg, to send over someone to work on stopping him. Andrea's motive was that her niece was one of over a hundred people who's blood was made to make the painting at Freddy's warehouse. The District Attorney contacted Matt Murdock to work on the getting Freddy and his son Patrick's gallery shut down.

It was all for naught however as Muse broke back into the warehouse and destroyed the piece while also leaving an address to his next work of art.
name: Frederick Durnin

description:
Chaos!

Checkers was an inmate back at Widmark state penitentiary during Ernest's time as a deathrow inmate there. When the nuke was dropped over the prison incinerating the surrounding area, she and 5 other inmates were reanimated by the power of Lady Hel and lead by fellow jailbird Homicide as a deterrent to an opposing group of monster teens called The Chosen. Having them on the ropes one of their number; who'ed later be revealed to be more than appearances let on, singlehandedly dispatched them back to the grave.

Last Ditch Bitch

Checkers and the other Dead Onez would later be revived and sent to collect the latest gem in the eye of their divine lady. From her dream limbo she resuscitated the toxic zombies and sent them after a descendant of Hel's guard dog by the name of Liv Halvorsen, she along with the others of corpse party ransacked her consent killing and slaughtering all of the rave goers attending. All while their lord herself possessed the rest of Liv's band in order to coax her into committing suicide.
name: Dani Matrix
